"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells..md#Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells. To date, curcumin is the most potent, natural antioxidant to inhibit the proliferation of cancer cells while inducing apoptosis. It has a similar structure to fatty acids and because one of HSA's main duties is to transport insoluble fatty acids, it binds easily to curcumin. Other studies have demonstrated that [[PDL-1 binding peptides conjugated to Curcumin-loaded ANCs increases cellular uptake while enhancing cyototoxic effects on PDL-1 expressing cancer cells.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Curcumin-loaded HSA nanoparticles have been found to increase the toxicity of these carriers to tumour tissue without damaging normal cells..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479451594,"size":887,"hash":"8477a197ba0003ce0a4f3260963070715ea15a40a9f27a2e2d19277c610ce59a"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.01095919,0.00681684,-0.02279523,0.04321619,0.04723765,-0.00181065,-0.00796618,-0.03146318,-0.00950817,0.00595719,-0.00921277,-0.03628053,-0.03492047,-0.04980738,0.02908072,0.00371071,0.02955605,-0.01719095,-0.00948303,-0.01428319,0.07266323,0.00946393,-0.011227,0.0235838,-0.06629907,-0.02402211,0.01098655,0.0076